               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1808">Internally dated to the year <foreign xml:lang="ta">palapava</foreign> of the Jovian cycle, that is (?), <foreign xml:lang="ta">pirapava</foreign> (Skt. <foreign xml:lang="sa">prabhava</foreign>), that is, CE 1867-1868, 1807-1808, 1747-1748, 1687-1688, etc. Bundle dated to circa 1830 by Vinson (1867) and to 1830 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably palaeographical and material analysis arguments). Not after 1854, since part of the collection of <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854), bequested in 1855 to the Société Asiatique, Paris (Rosny 1868).</origDate>
                     <origPlace>Tamilnadu.</origPlace>
